      "source": [
        "# 🖊️ Pen & Highlighter Detector — Training Notebook\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook trains a **YOLOv8** object detection model to detect and classify **pens** and **highlighters** in real time using a custom labeled dataset from Roboflow.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 📋 Steps to Follow\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Google Colab with **T4 GPU** enabled (Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU)\n",
        "2. **Install dependencies** — install `ultralytics` and `roboflow` packages\n",
        "23 **Get your dataset** — create or fork a dataset on [Roboflow](https://roboflow.com), generate a version, and export via the code snippet provided\n",
        "4. **Paste your Roboflow snippet** — replace `YOUR_ROBOFLOW_API_KEY` with your own key from Roboflow settings\n",
        "5. **Run training** — execute the training cell to fine-tune YOLOv8n on your dataset (GPU recommended)\n",
        "6. **Download `best.pt`** — save your trained model weights to use locally\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
